  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Considering Implementation**\n\nI\'m thrilled with the initial build\'s success! Now I\'m focusing on implementation. The user desires an interactive single-page application \342\200\223 a visually stunning, AAA game-style learning web app for AI Engineering. I\'m currently reviewing the necessary features: a header with a logo and the application\'s name is a must.\n\n\n**Planning Game Structure**\n\nI\'ve been mapping out the game\'s core structure, prioritizing user engagement. I\'m focusing on integrating an XP system with a progress bar and level badges. The hero section will feature an AI mascot, \"AIKO,\" providing friendly guidance with dynamic expressions. Next, I\'m defining the game hub with six mini-game cards, each focused on a specific AI concept.\n\n\n**Defining Achievement Structure**\n\nI\'m now diving into achievement badges, thinking about specific milestones. I\'ve brainstormed a basic set of six, like \"First Neuron\" and \"AI Master,\" which seem like a good starting point. I\'m adding six more to reach a total of twelve, focusing on varied challenges and concepts, such as \"Speed Demon,\" \"Network Master,\" and \"Aiko\'s Friend.\" I\'m also planning to create a badge for reaching Level 6.\n\n\n**Establishing Visual Framework**\n\nI\'ve established the visual styling guidelines, focusing on a deep-space color palette with neon accents. I\'m leveraging Orbitron, Inter, and JetBrains Mono for a distinct typographic hierarchy. The plan includes particle backgrounds, hover glows, dynamic progress bars, and confetti bursts for correct answers, all utilizing the Web Audio API. I intend to use HTML5, CSS3, and vanilla JavaScript for a strong core experience.\n\n\n**Integrating Interactive Elements**\n\nI\'m now integrating interactive elements, focusing on the Canvas API for \"Neuron Builder\" and \"Overfitting Escape\" mini-games. I\'m also implementing sound cues using the Web Audio API for correct/incorrect answers, level-ups, and button presses. Mobile responsiveness is paramount. Finally, I\'m injecting warm, conversational Indonesian phrases, such as \"Waduh, overfitting nih!\" and \"Oke mantap!\" into the experience, along with my AI mascot, \"AIKO.\"\n\n\n**Prioritizing Inlining**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on a crucial point: the project must be a single `index.html` file with everything inline. No external files are permitted, save for the Google Fonts CDN. This means I\'ll write styles directly within the `<style>` block, crafting a custom, modern CSS theme using variables, Flexbox, grids, and neon utility classes. I\'m focusing on ensuring a high-fidelity standalone experience, even without Tailwind, by default.\n\n\n**Refining Standalone Approach**\n\nI\'m now completely sold on custom CSS for the single-file requirement! It\'s elegant, self-sufficient, and ensures true standalone functionality, especially offline. I\'m focusing on crafting high-quality, neon-infused custom styles with variables, responsive grids, and transitions. I\'m building semantic HTML with a custom `<style>` block for layout and UI elements, which ensures everything renders perfectly. I\'m also reviewing how this impacts the Vite setup, and ensuring `index.html` loads static resources correctly.\n\n\n**Confirming Project Structure**\n\nI\'m now confirming the project structure with Vite. I\'ve realized that Vite handles `/index.html` as the entry point automatically. If it doesn\'t import React code, it serves it statically, along with any assets. I\'m considering minimal script references in the HTML, or making the HTML completely inline with CSS and JS. I\'m also preparing to test `npm run build` and ensure the project builds correctly. I need to make sure `src/main.tsx` and `src/App.tsx` are error-free.\n\n\n**Validating File Integrity**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the integrity of the project files, especially in relation to the `index.html` file and Vite. I\'ve realized that the `src/main.tsx` and `src/App.tsx` files can either be kept simple and valid for compilation, or eliminated from the `index.html` file, allowing Vite to ignore them during the build process, which will not interfere with the final product. I\'ll ensure they are clean, valid, and compilation-friendly.\n\n\n**Confirming Typechecking Behavior**\n\nI\'ve verified `tsc --noEmit` still runs over `src/` files even if they\'re not used, perfect! Keeping `src/App.tsx` and `src/main.tsx` clean and simple ensures type-checking passes. The project will now be built directly in `index.html` to satisfy the single-file, inline requirement. I\'ll design the visual and functional aspects of the **AI Engineering Interactive Mini-Games Arena** in `/index.html`. I\'ll start by listing the necessary CSS custom properties within the `<style>` tag.\n\n\n**Designing Interface Aesthetics**\n\nI\'m now detailing visual elements. I plan to use Google Fonts (Orbitron, Inter, JetBrains Mono) and a deep-space color palette with neon accents to create a visually striking interface. I\'m focusing on the canvas particle background with glowing dots and the neon XP progress bar. Six detailed game cards with neon hover effects, interactive icons, hover glow lines, and completion badges are being conceptualized. Aiko, the AI mascot, will feature interactive speech bubbles and rendered SVG expressions.\n\n\n**Developing Game Arena**\n\nI\'m now focusing on a \"Game Arena\" modal overlay for each mini-game. These will offer custom configurations, detailed AI concept explanations via typewriter effects, and fully interactive canvas experiences for specific games, like \"Neuron Builder\" and \"Overfitting Escape.\" I\'m also implementing audio synthesizer cues for feedback. The design includes a Leaderboard and Achievements Drawer with 12 collectible, glowing badges and funny AI historical characters with competitive scores.\n\n\n\n**Implementing Neuron Builder**\n\nI\'m now implementing the \"Neuron Builder\" mini-game. I\'m focusing on the canvas-based interactive workspace with node anchors representing neurons across three columns. Players can drag lines between neurons to build synapses, complete with lightning sparks and hum sounds. I\'m also ensuring the \"Network Strength\" progress bar climbs as connections are made and the **Boss Challenge** triggers upon 100% connectivity. I\'ve designed a multiple-choice visual Boss Challenge to handle a scenario of negative home price prediction.\n\n\n**Expanding Game Data**\n\nI\'m now detailing the Data Sorter mini-game\'s data points. I\'m focusing on crafting a variety of drawings and emojis within Polaroid frames. This game will focus on training data, labeling, and the concept of \"garbage in, garbage out\". I\'m creating a diverse set of images: cats, dogs, cars, food items, and even ambiguous data like a chocolate muffin versus a cupcake.\n\n\n**Defining Data Sorter**\n\nI\'m now integrating new image data for the \"Data Sorter\" mini-game, focusing on real-world examples and potential biases. I\'ve designed a diverse set, including the classic muffin/chihuahua meme, toy cars versus real cars, and intentionally blurred or corrupted images to highlight bad data\'s impact. The gameplay involves rapid labeling with a shrinking timer and rewards for accuracy. Starting at Level 3, I\'m introducing a \"SKIP/CORRUPTED\" button to simulate real-world data cleaning. Correct labels boost a neural network accuracy gauge, yielding XP and new badges.\n\n\n**Crafting a Coding Poem**\n\nI\'m now integrating a new element: a \"Poetry Prompt\" mini-game. This new feature will guide users to compose a short poem about code. I\'m focusing on crafting a prompt-block-based system to guide them. I\'ll include various blocks: \"ROLE\", \"TASK\", \"CONSTRAINT\", and \"FORMAT\". Each block will feature creative writing prompts inspired by Pujangga Baru\'s classic poetry. I am using a drag-and-drop interaction, as well as an area to review and iterate on outputs. The goal is to make a fun, educational, and poetic coding experience.\n\n\n**Refining Prompt Poem**\n\nI\'m now implementing the \"Poetry Prompt\" mini-game with new features and refined prompts. I\'m dynamically scoring block selections for an elegant AI response, and adding a poem: \"Dalam hening malam, aksara menari...\" I\'m assigning +150 XP and unlocking \"Perfect Prompt.\" Now I am focusing on GAME 4, \"Model Showdown,\" with supervised vs unsupervised learning types, an arena of model cards, and challenging real-world scenarios.\n\n\n**Defining Model Showdown**\n\nI\'m now detailing **Game 4**: \"Model Showdown,\" with supervised vs. unsupervised learning scenarios, and I have five game challenges defined. *Tantangan 1* is for regression, while *Tantangan 2 and 5* focus on classification, and *Tantangan 3* is for clustering. The goal is to provide a varied and engaging experience, and correct answers lead to a cosmic showdown animation. Achieving a 5-streak victory will unlock both the \"AI Master\" and \"Gladiator\" badges.\n\n\n\n**Visualizing Generalization**\n\nI\'m now implementing Game 5, \"Overfitting Escape,\" and visualizing underfitting, overfitting, and generalization using a neon grid maze within a `<canvas>` element. The AI robot navigates a maze with adjustable model complexity via a slider (1-10), and the robot\342\200\231s path reveals underfitting at low complexity, overfitting at high complexity, and generalization at the perfect setting. A real-time training loss graph also provides instant visual feedback.\n\n\n**Evaluating Ethical AI**\n\nI\'m now implementing the sixth mini-game, \"Ethical AI Judge.\" I\'m creating a courtroom scene with comic panels to present ethically challenging cases involving bias, transparency, and privacy. The player will judge dynamic cases and choose between actions. Correct choices will get XP rewards and clear explanations. A visual \"Law & Order\" sound effect will play on each choice, and each selection displays a response from the court system with a score.\n\n\n**Synthesizing Audio Cues**\n\nI\'m developing custom sound cues using the Web Audio API for feedback: a major triad for success, a low buzz for errors, a frequency sweep for level-ups, and a short ping for clicks. My goal is to craft these sounds directly in JavaScript with zero external file dependencies. This will ensure all audio elements work seamlessly within the inline single-file approach.\n\n\n\n**Integrating Tailwind Styles**\n\nI\'m now integrating Tailwind into the inline setup to preview the design flawlessly. I\'m focusing on crafting robust inline styles within the `<style>` tag, and ensuring that they play nicely with the compiled Tailwind styles in `/src/index.css` via Vite, resulting in both an excellent preview and a compliant, standalone `index.html` file.\n\n\n**Persisting User Progress**\n\nI\'m now integrating `localStorage` for state management, serializing the score, level, achievements, active games, and any current tips. This will persist progress across reloads. I\'m also planning the interface hierarchy, starting with a root element and focusing on a futuristic design with a particle background and a main app container.\n\n\n**Designing Interactive Dashboard**\n\nI\'m now detailing the right-side dashboard\'s features. I will include an active, glowing Level Badge (\"Lv. 1 - AI Newbie\"), an XP Indicator (\"45 / 100 XP\"), and a glowing, animated XP Progress Tracker Bar. This section aims for a futuristic design with particle backgrounds and a main app container. I will create a cute introduction greeting box featuring AIKO, the robot mascot sidekick, and a grid for the six mini-games.\n\n\n\n**Adding Interactive Chat**\n\nI\'m now integrating an interactive chat console where users can ask \"AIKO\" machine learning questions, instantly receiving hilarious, insightful Indonesian educational responses. I\'m focusing on a local keyword detector for frequent questions and answers, and including a real typewriter effect. I am also working on adding a global leaderboard with player stats and a vault of twelve high-contrast, lockable badges.\n\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 36
      nanos: 502018974
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
