e the sound synthesizing function ready to go.\n\n\n**Implementing Sound Effects**\n\nI\'ve completed the sound design, with distinct JavaScript functions for \"error,\" \"click,\" and \"levelUp\" sounds, each featuring unique oscillator and gain settings. I am now focused on integrating these sounds into various game events and synthesizing audio through Web Audio API. I am planning to test the integration by triggering different synthesized sound effects for each mini-game interaction.\n\n\n**Developing Canvas Interactions**\n\nI\'m now focusing on ensuring that the canvas mini-games function correctly, specifically the Neuron Builder and Data Sorter. I\'m implementing node rendering, glowing paths for connections, and mouse event listeners for the Neuron Builder. The Data Sorter now features emoji/polaroid styled images with border-glows, along with a shrinking time bar and dynamic charts reflecting accuracy changes. \"Bias alerts\" will challenge the user.\n\n\n**Designing New Games**\n\nI\'m now outlining some new mini-games. \"Wizard Game\" involves selecting blocks to build spell chains, with animations for casting. \"Model Showdown\" will showcase real-world datasets with engaging VS animations and badge releases. Lastly, \"Overfitting Escape\" is a canvas-based game where the user adjusts a complexity slider to navigate a grid corridor, demonstrating underfitting, overfitting, and generalist paths.\n\n\n**Adding the Loss Curves**\n\nI\'m now incorporating an interactive, live-updating chart that displays Training vs. Validation loss curves, correlating to the complexity slider\'s position in \"Overfitting Escape.\" This visual feedback will provide a critical real-time understanding of the model\'s behavior. I\'m also preparing the ethical AI judge mini-game, with its review dialogues and unlockable features. The next step is to write all of this into `/index.html`.\n\n\n"
