e now includes frequency values for a C4-G4-C5 arpeggio.\n\n\n**Refining Audio Effects**\n\nI\'m now refining the audio synthesis implementation. I\'ve defined distinct sounds for different actions; I\'m generating a rising sine sweep for level-ups, decaying sawtooth for errors, a quick sine click for interactions, and the arpeggio for success. Each sound is precisely timed using exponential ramps for a polished experience.\n\n\n**Designing Responsive Layout**\n\nI\'m now focusing on drafting the layout, specifically the HTML file. I\'m prioritizing responsiveness and aesthetics, thinking about Google Font imports (Orbitron, Inter, and JetBrains Mono). My goal is to write high-quality markup in `index.html` with clean classes. I\'m exploring Tailwind elements with custom animations (pulse-blue, glow-neon, shake-effect, float-around, shimmering) to create a visually appealing, responsive game experience. The HTML structure will include a header for the logo and game title. I aim to create a powerful single HTML file.\n\n\n**Structuring Game Display**\n\nI\'m now deep in thought about the game\'s UI structure, focusing on a Bento layout for the main container. I plan a grid-based approach with columns for the game cards and side panels. AIKO, the AI mascot, will have an interactive chatbot console, and I\'ll implement leaderboards and achievements, with 6 game modals.\n\n\n**Constructing the HTML File**\n\nI\'m now diving deep into designing the `index.html` file. I\'m prioritizing a visually stunning, interactive, and efficient implementation, aiming for instant loading and avoiding token limits. The goal is to produce a beautiful, error-free HTML structure via the `create_file` method with `Overwrite: true` to replace the existing file entirely.\n\n\n"
