    thinking: "**Modularizing Game Architecture**\n\nI\'m making good headway in structuring the interactive games as modular components. The goal is to keep `App.tsx` streamlined and ensure each game has its own clean, maintainable code base. I\'m focusing on beautiful, inline layouts for each game. I\'m aiming for elegance and maintainability.\n\n\n**Designing Neuron Builder**\n\nI\'ve started building the \"Neuron Builder\" game as `src/components/NeuronBuilder.tsx`. The core mechanic involves connecting nodes (input, hidden, and output) with visual and auditory feedback. I\'m leaning toward an SVG-based canvas for interactive connections with electric spark visuals, including glowing neon circles and shiny connectors. A \"Network Strength\" meter will update as connections are made. I am also planning on building in a boss challenge!\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I am creating `/src/components/NeuronBuilder.tsx` to build Game 1 (\"Neuron Builder\") representing Neural Networks. It will feature an interactive neural diagram (Input, Hidden, Output layers) rendered beautifully with glowing SVG nodes and active laser sparks, live connection rules, continuous \"Network Strength\" percentage metrics, and a visual multiple-choice Boss Challenge in Indonesian highlighting real training failures."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 2
      nanos: 356785846
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
