  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing the Second Game**\n\nI\'m now fully immersed in developing \"Data Sorter.\" My concept focuses on training data, labeling, and bias, visualized through Polaroid-style image cards. Each card will represent a data point, using emojis like a cat, dog, car, or phone, to make it visually engaging. This is starting to take shape really nicely!\n\n\n**Defining Data Points**\n\nI\'ve been refining the data point specifics for \"Data Sorter.\" I\'m planning interactive clicks with Hewan \360\237\246\201, Kendaraan \360\237\232\232, Gadget \360\237\223\261, and FLAG \360\237\232\253 to mark corrupt data. I\'m building a system where players label data under a timer, with level-ups for accuracy. I am going to include ambiguous data points in later levels to mock real-world bias, and the use of \'SKIP/FLAG\' for corrupt data. My plan is to include localStorage to track labeled items.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I am creating `/src/components/DataSorter.tsx` to build Game 2 (\"Data Sorter\") centered on Training Data, Labeling, & Bias. It features Polaroid-style visual cards, high-velocity click matching buttons with sliding timer bars, noise skips/flags, and live accuracy indicators using inline metrics. It updates persistent label stats and reports back with custom progress triggers."
