  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Designing the UI**\n\nI\'ve been envisioning a top-tier game studio UI aesthetic for this. Think beautiful, glowing borders, high-fidelity visuals, and elegant typography. I\'m exploring responsive padding and rhythmic neon borders to tie it all together.\n\n\n**Building the Sandbox**\n\nI\'m now focused on the component `/src/components/HyperparameterSandbox.tsx`. The goal is extreme visual polish. It\'ll allow users to manipulate hyperparameters and see prompt responses. It\'ll have controls for Temperature, Top-P, and Frequency Penalty, alongside a System Prompt field for persona setting. I\'m also including a drop-down to choose between Gemini-3.5-Flash, DeepSeek-R1, and Llama-3-70B models.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I will now write a comprehensive, feature-rich, and visually spectacular component `/src/components/HyperparameterSandbox.tsx`. This adds the highly requested feature of a **Model & Hyperparameter Tuning Playground**. In this playground, students can adjust real Core LLM hyperparameters (Temperature, Top-P, Frequency Penalty, System Prompt) and choose models (like Google Gemini-Flash or DeepSeek R1 with visible reasoning chains). This lets them see how parameters directly shape AI creativity, repetition, and logic. Let\'s create this file with complete self-contained logic and clean UI styling."
